00:13:56.638 --> 00:14:01.440
So successful game developers,
we know, deploy sophisticated

00:14:01.440 --> 00:14:03.020
monetization models
for their games,

00:14:03.020 --> 00:14:07.181
and ads play a really important
role in that exercise.

00:14:07.181 --> 00:14:09.430
When you think about a good
ads monetization strategy,

00:14:09.430 --> 00:14:11.260
it really depends on
these three things.

00:14:11.260 --> 00:14:14.076
One is you need to understand
your users in a very deep way.

00:14:14.076 --> 00:14:15.700
You want to be able
to tailor your game

00:14:15.700 --> 00:14:19.700
experiences to those audiences
and react to how they behave.

00:14:19.700 --> 00:14:22.516
Second is you want to show
ads at the right time,

00:14:22.516 --> 00:14:24.140
and this is so you
can maximize revenue

00:14:24.140 --> 00:14:26.580
for people who are
likely to spend, and also

00:14:26.580 --> 00:14:28.100
have a variety of ad formats.

00:14:28.100 --> 00:14:29.590
And those ad formats
help you find

00:14:29.590 --> 00:14:31.850
the balance between
when you show an ad

00:14:31.850 --> 00:14:35.250
and how you keep users
properly engaged in your game.

00:14:35.250 --> 00:14:37.822
Now, if you've gone through
the exercise of thinking

00:14:37.822 --> 00:14:40.030
about building this yourself,
or if you've done that,

00:14:40.030 --> 00:14:42.840
you know it's a big investment,
both in software engineering

00:14:42.840 --> 00:14:44.830
resources, know-how,
and not to mention,

00:14:44.830 --> 00:14:46.470
the back-end infrastructure.

00:14:46.470 --> 00:14:50.340
Meanwhile, AdMob can provide
all these tools that you need,

00:14:50.340 --> 00:14:53.200
and I'm excited to share with
you three big announcements

00:14:53.200 --> 00:14:56.240
for ads that represent,
really, a platform

00:14:56.240 --> 00:15:00.850
that's a smart, audience-aware
platform for showing

00:15:00.850 --> 00:15:03.070
the right ads to your players.

00:15:03.070 --> 00:15:05.500
The first of these tools
is called Audience Builder.

00:15:05.500 --> 00:15:07.760
It's now available to
all AdMob developers

00:15:07.760 --> 00:15:11.920
who use Google Play Analytics,
or Google Analytics globally.

00:15:11.920 --> 00:15:14.460
Audience Builder through
AdMob is this way

00:15:14.460 --> 00:15:16.900
of creating a list of
users, or audience lists,

00:15:16.900 --> 00:15:19.890
based on Google
Analytics segments.

00:15:19.890 --> 00:15:23.250
These can be based on behaviors,
like sessions or spending.

00:15:23.250 --> 00:15:26.270
And it enables you to play
with different monetization

00:15:26.270 --> 00:15:27.610
strategies with those users.

00:15:27.610 --> 00:15:29.910
So a canonical example
might be taking

00:15:29.910 --> 00:15:31.860
a segment of users
that were previously

00:15:31.860 --> 00:15:34.742
paying users who had
churned out after 30 days,

00:15:34.742 --> 00:15:36.200
creating an audience
list for them,

00:15:36.200 --> 00:15:38.970
and then creating an ad campaign
to try to attract them back

00:15:38.970 --> 00:15:41.070
to your game.

00:15:41.070 --> 00:15:44.380
The second tool is called
In-App Purchase House Ads.

00:15:44.380 --> 00:15:46.720
House Ads are, as
some of you know,

00:15:46.720 --> 00:15:48.530
free ads that you
display in your game

00:15:48.530 --> 00:15:51.860
to promote in-game items and
consumables that players might

00:15:51.860 --> 00:15:53.790
want to enhance their gameplay.

00:15:53.790 --> 00:15:55.490
A challenge with
House Ads, of course,

00:15:55.490 --> 00:15:58.230
though, is that everybody's in
a different stage in your game.

00:15:58.230 --> 00:16:00.520
Early players are
probably going to be

00:16:00.520 --> 00:16:03.590
interested in a different
set of purchasable items,

00:16:03.590 --> 00:16:06.360
versus advanced players
who may be more nuanced.

00:16:06.360 --> 00:16:09.430
AdMob solves this with
Google algorithms and machine

00:16:09.430 --> 00:16:12.240
learning to only show
these types of ads

00:16:12.240 --> 00:16:15.090
to users who are likely
to take advantage of them.

00:16:15.090 --> 00:16:17.160
We do all that work
for you so players

00:16:17.160 --> 00:16:19.980
can get the ad that they
want, and for everybody else,

00:16:19.980 --> 00:16:23.500
you can focus on creating
a different experience.

00:16:23.500 --> 00:16:25.640
And lastly, we're incredibly
excited to announce

00:16:25.640 --> 00:16:28.050
a new format,
Native Ads, which is

00:16:28.050 --> 00:16:30.130
available through
a limited beta.

00:16:30.130 --> 00:16:32.790
Native Ads is this
popular industry term

00:16:32.790 --> 00:16:35.300
that's used to describe an ad
experience that essentially

00:16:35.300 --> 00:16:37.800
weaves into the product's
form and function

00:16:37.800 --> 00:16:39.560
so it looks like it belongs.

00:16:39.560 --> 00:16:41.650
Google has a lot of
experience doing this well,

00:16:41.650 --> 00:16:43.880
and we're bringing that
capability to game developers

00:16:43.880 --> 00:16:45.100
today.

00:16:45.100 --> 00:16:48.730
Native Ads benefits users,
advertisers, and developers.

00:16:48.730 --> 00:16:51.230
From a user experience, it
is a better user experience

00:16:51.230 --> 00:16:53.910
when the ad looks like it
actually belongs in your game.

00:16:53.910 --> 00:16:56.250
And advertisers see
stronger, or can

00:16:56.250 --> 00:16:58.120
see stronger,
performance when it looks

00:16:58.120 --> 00:17:00.190
like it's natively styled.

00:17:00.190 --> 00:17:02.219
And as a developer,
you get to preserve

00:17:02.219 --> 00:17:04.010
more of the creative
direction of your game

00:17:04.010 --> 00:17:06.189
when you add ads
into your experience,

00:17:06.189 --> 00:17:08.480
while gaining the benefits
of the revenue opportunities

00:17:08.480 --> 00:17:10.703
that ads can provide you.

