00:18:05.290 --> 00:18:08.690
We launched Android TV at
Google I/O in June of last year,

00:18:08.690 --> 00:18:11.050
bringing Android into the
living room for big screen

00:18:11.050 --> 00:18:13.190
apps, games, and content.

00:18:13.190 --> 00:18:15.910
It's controlled easily
through voice and remote,

00:18:15.910 --> 00:18:19.260
and as a platform, it's going
to come in a variety of flavors.

00:18:19.260 --> 00:18:22.130
You're going to see it on
smart TVs, microconsoles,

00:18:22.130 --> 00:18:24.300
and set-top boxes.

00:18:24.300 --> 00:18:26.820
This year, we're really excited
about the ecosystem that's

00:18:26.820 --> 00:18:29.750
growing, and OEMs are bringing
those different form factors

00:18:29.750 --> 00:18:31.930
to the world that all
use the same operating

00:18:31.930 --> 00:18:33.300
system and experience.

00:18:33.300 --> 00:18:36.190
And that alone is
a unique phenomenon

00:18:36.190 --> 00:18:38.666
when you think about the
history of the living room.

00:18:38.666 --> 00:18:40.290
And a lot of partners
are going all in.

