00:25:00.897 --> 00:25:03.480
Let me talk about Project Tango,
which is in developer preview

00:25:03.480 --> 00:25:04.410
right now.

00:25:04.410 --> 00:25:06.960
This is a project from our
advanced technology group

00:25:06.960 --> 00:25:08.660
that's attempting
to give devices

00:25:08.660 --> 00:25:10.667
an understanding of
space and motion.

00:25:10.667 --> 00:25:13.000
So when you think about it,
you can walk into this room,

00:25:13.000 --> 00:25:15.360
and you have an understanding
of the walls around you,

00:25:15.360 --> 00:25:16.610
the chairs, the people.

00:25:16.610 --> 00:25:18.860
And that's how you
negotiate around the room.

00:25:18.860 --> 00:25:22.110
We want to give devices a
similar kind of understanding.

00:25:22.110 --> 00:25:25.100
And so Project Tango does this
by adding another wide camera

00:25:25.100 --> 00:25:28.630
lens to a device, a
depth-sensing camera,

00:25:28.630 --> 00:25:30.820
and a software stack that
gives you access to all

00:25:30.820 --> 00:25:32.622
